Yet another refinement of our upgraded Eta code is the enforcement of the Arakawa-type conservation in the vertical diffusion. This is done using the standard technique (e.g., Arakawa and Lamb 1977) of writing the advective form of a difference equation so that it is equivalent to its flux form. For example, in case of the diffusion contribution to the time change of specific humidity, q, this amounts to replacing (5.1) of Janjic (1990) by\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
