Once most of the physics package of the Eta was put together at the end of the 1980s (Janjic 1990) in tests that followed a conspicuous problem encountered was that of runaway convection over warm water. This was addressed in Janjic (1994) by modifications of the Betts-Miller convection scheme via implementation of two mechanisms sensitive to the intensity of convection. The first included introduction of a nondimensional parameter17\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
