The “surface renewal theory” (e.g., LKB, or SCOR WG 110, 2000, Sect. 7.3.2 C) postulates the existence of small eddies which intermittently transfer heat, etc. across the transition layer between the molecular and the fully turbulent layer. LKB have shown that Brutsaert’s suggestion of the renewal time scale of these eddies being proportional to the time scale of the Kolmogorov eddies leads to21\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
